FYI `let onlineUsers = {}` needs to be declared at the top of app.js and outside of the `io.on('connection, [...])` function.

Otherwise, onlineUsers will not persist. So if you refresh, onlineUsers will be blank.

Before:

```
// app.js

const io = require('<http://socket.io|socket.io>')(server);
let onlineUsers = {};
io.on("connection", (socket) =&gt; {
  require('./sockets/chat.js')(io, socket, onlineUsers);
})
```
After:

```
// app.js

let onlineUsers = {};

// <http://Socket.io|Socket.io>
let io = require('<http://socket.io|socket.io>').listen(server);
io.on('connection', (socket) =&gt; {
  require('./sockets/chat.js')(io, socket, onlineUsers);
});
```

